nodes.display_name: Synthesis of the novel transporter YdhC, is regulated by the YdhB transcription factor controlling adenosine and adenine uptake.
nodes.label: study

data.detail: A key regulatory step is the production of 5-phospho-α-D-ribosyl 1-pyrophosphate

YdhC is an uncharacterized member of the Drug:H+ Antiporter (DHA) Family within the Major Facilitator Superfamily (MFS) of transporters [Marger93, Saier16]. YdhC has been implicated in arabinose efflux [Koita12].
